post_text:
Good luck to our girls tonight as they travel to Paton-Churdan for JV/V volleyball!!!

A few guidelines to remember that Paton-Churdan has implemented for spectators:

1. All students in 8th grade and below are required to sit with parents.

2. We ask that all spectators sit in family units and social distance when possible. 9-12 students are asked to practice social distancing in the student section of the bleachers and wear masks.

3. We highly recommend that spectators wear masks especially when entering and exiting the gym and get up from their seat.

4. Please also remember that if a ball would go into the crowd, they cannot be thrown back to the players or line judge, they must be thrown back to a designated person to sanitize balls before they can return to play.

There will be a $5 admission for all ages & concessions/drinks are going to be prepackaged.

***Ar-We-Va High School Parents***

Our 9th-12th grade students daily Ar-We-Va schedules will not change. They will have their classes here every day. However, they do not have to be here on the days of their Carroll "off-site" learning until their Ar-We-Va classes start (11 AM for 9th/10th & 1 for 11th/12th). We do understand that some students ride the morning bus to school and/or need internet access. So, on the "off-site" days for Carroll, they can come here, and we will have a place for them to work. They will also still have lessons/assignments/activities to complete for Carroll courses on their off-site days.

post_text:
***COVID Update***

Due to an increase in positive cases and county positivity rates, Carroll High School is moving to an A-B hybrid model beginning Wednesday, September 2nd. Ar-We-Va students with last names A-L will be in group A, and students with last names M-Z will be in group B. Please see the following chart below for more information.

We will also be mandating that masks be worn during passing time in the halls as well as in the lunch line for all students K-12 beginning tomorrow, September1st. Students that do not have masks may come to the office and pick one up. Rates will continue to be monitored which may require additional measures to be put into place.

Ar-We-Va Football Guidelines

1) Masks are expected to be worn if social distancing is
not possible.

2) Children in grades K-8 are expected to sit with their
parents/guardians/adult. If students are there without a parent/guardian/adult, the parent will be called to pick up the student.

3) If you are paying at the gate, please use the exact change. Admission is $5.00 per person.....K-Adult

4) Spectators sitting on the south hill should social distance.

5) Fans should practice social distancing between different household units

6) Anyone that has a fever or Covid-19 related symptoms or has been exposed to someone that is Covid-19 positive should NOT attend the game.

From the nurse's desk

Hello parents and students! As we get started into the new school year, I know there are many emotions involved for everyone. Even though these times are challenging, we will get through it and learn so much from it! Parents and guardians, I ask that you please err on the side of caution in regards to sending your child to school or keeping them home when ill for the safety and health of everyone. I have attached a link of signs/symptoms and return to school guidelines based on the Iowa Department of Public Health. Let’s all work together to have a healthy and fantastic year!

Mary Rohe, RN
School Nurse
maryrohe@ar-we-va.k12.ia.us

post_text: While every occupation has its stress levels - none can compare to that of a school administrator during these last few weeks before school starts. . . .it's one of those jobs where you are only right about 50% of the time to about 50% of the people. While I can testify that they are getting very little sleep (I actually received an email this morning at 3am from our administrator!) they are also doing a tremendous job!! Hang in there school administrators! We all appreciate everything you're doing for our kids during these crazy times!!!

Information for district baseball on Saturday:

IKMM-BV scheduled for 4:30 PM. AWV-Audubon scheduled for 7 PM. IKMM and Audubon will be using the 1st base dugouts and be the home team. BV and Ar-We-Va will be in the 3rd base dugouts and be the away team. Please park all buses on the east side of the football field/track. You can enter from the street on the east (3rd Ave). Remind your fans that admission is $6 for everyone. If possible please bring exact change. Conference/school passes won’t be accepted. Ar-We-Va please tell your fans to not show up until 6:30 or later. We will NOT start the 2nd game until at the earliest 7 PM. We are highly encouraged to get the crowd from the first game out of there as much as possible, and keep fans from the second game from showing up too early.

WHAT IS THE PANDEMIC ELECTRONIC BENEFIT TRANSFER (P-EBT) PROGRAM? -The Families First CoronaVirus Act allows states to issue Food Assistance benefits to households with
children in Pre-K through 12th grade who lost access to Free and Reduced Price School Meals due to
pandemic-related school closures in Spring 2020.

Click on the link below for more information

TECHNOLOGY ACCESS SURVEY

Ar-We-Va families,

Please read the attached information about a statewide technology access survey. Each household is being asked to complete this survey, and it could have an impact on funding we receive for technology purposes. The survey deadline is June 24th. If you have any questions or concerns, please email cpetersen@ar-we-va.k12.ia.us. The responses from this survey will help prioritize $26.2 million in federal relief through the Governor’s Emergency Education Relief (GEER), which focuses on providing and expanding broadband access and improving access to technology in other ways.The link is provided in the information attached.

Thanks

post_text:
Rocket baseball and softball fans:

We have finally begun another sports season in Iowa! Practices for baseball and softball kicked off yesterday, and coaches and players were more than excited to get back to some normalcy. While we know this is a great step to return back to the things that we love, we must also take the necessary steps and measures to ensure this return is done in the safest manner possible. Here is a link to guidance from the boys association/girls union on both practice and game protocol. You will also see the following signage posted at all of our games. Please help us to ensure we can provide the safest environment possible for players, spectators, and coaches.

https://www.iahsaa.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Iowa-DE-Guidance-Summer-Sports-5.20.20.pdf

Ar-We-Va students, parents, and community:

First and foremost, we want to thank everyone for their patience during this unprecedented time. We understand this has been a difficult time for students, teachers, and families alike with a great amount of uncertainty about a number of school-related events (graduation, prom, final grades, etc.). The following document addresses many of those events, and how we will proceed with them as a district. We will continue to push out updated information as it is available. This information, along with more specifics, will also be provided on our district website.

We want to thank all of our teachers, staff, and volunteers who have continued to work together to provide meals, academic engagement opportunities, and support to our students and families during this time.

Thank You!

School will continue through a continuous learning model for the rest of the academic year due to the governor’s recent closure for the 19-20 school year. Spring sports have been cancelled, and a decision about summer sports will be made by June 1st. Please be patient as we know there are many questions about a number of topics. We will continue to push information out through our website, social media, and notification system.

post_text:
No Food Service Program Dates

There will be no food service program on Friday, April 10, 2020 through Tuesday, April 14, 2020. These days were a scheduled break in the school calendar; therefore, the district is unable to provide meals due to the rules of the program. The food service program will resume on Wednesday, April 15, 2020.

Due to the unprecedented times, the food service program is subject to change at any time.

If you have not already signed up for the Grab 'n Go Meals for your children 1 to 18 or have questions, please email lwieland@ar-we-va.k12.ia.us or stickrod@ar-we-va.k12.ia.us with the number of children between the ages of 1 to 18 in your household, pickup location, and your name. Quantities each day may be limited due to the supplies on hand and current demand.

This institution is an equal opportunity provider.

post_text:
TO: ALL 6TH & 7TH GRADE FAMILIES

We will be distributing your student’s school issued chromebooks on Monday, April 6, from 5:30-6 PM and again on Tuesday, April 7, from 7-7:30 AM. These will be distributed in a drive-thru format. We will have people outside of the elementary entrance with those computers to hand to you in your vehicle. In order to maintain social distancing guidelines, please do not get out of your vehicle. It is also best if there is no one sitting in the passenger’s seat of the vehicle so that we can simply set the chromebook on the passenger seat of the vehicle. We are issuing these as we move to a distance learning model that will involve a heavy online format for our 6th-12th grade students. We will post information in the coming days about those courses and resources through our website as well as our Facebook page.

On Tuesday, April 7th, the Ar-We-Va School will be doing a staff car parade throughout Vail, Westside, and Arcadia starting at 9:00 am. The teachers are meeting at the school parking lot at 8:50 am Tuesday morning, we will be LEAVING the school parking lot to head to Vail right at 9. The tentative timeline is 9:10 enter Vail, 9:30 leave Vail, 9:45 enter Westside, 10:05 leave Westside, 10:15 enter Arcadia, 10:40 leave Arcadia to head back to school. We will drive through, honk, wave and tell the students how much we miss them. We encourage everyone to respect the 6-foot rule as we are practicing social distancing. Please no running up to the vehicles to give hugs or high fives. For reference we will be using the Westside and Vail parade routes and the Arcadia route will go past the park and through Front Street. Out of town kids may come in and sit at the parks or on Mainstreet.

If you have any questions or we need to add more information just let us know!
Thanks again!

post_text:
***ATTENTION: All students in DMACC classes.***
Attached you will find a document that outlines some of the DMACC policies that have been amended for the spring 2020 semester. We realize that there is a lot of concern amongst students with having to move instruction online, so we are trying to be flexible and provide additional options.

The two policies addressed in the handout include extensions to the drop dates and also the option to let students choose a Pass/Fail grade after the semester ends. I am asking students to contact me before they choose the pass/fail option as some courses/programs will not accept these grades for pre-requisites or for the program. A quick example of that would be our nursing program requires that students must pass each class with a C or better, so a P grade would not qualify students to have met that minimum.

post_text:
***COACH BELL INDUCTED INTO IHSAA BASKETBALL HALL OF FAME***

Coach Tim Bell coached and taught for 39 years, all at Ar-We-Va. He compiled a 527-302 record before retiring at the end of the 2015-16 season. Twenty-eight of his teams had winning seasons, and seven won over 20 games. His last team won 57 regular season games in a row and had lost only one conference game in the newly-formed Rolling Valley Conference in its first three years. His teams won 12 conference championships including one his first year in 1977-78 and the last three before his retirement. Three times, his teams’ seasons ended as Substate runners-up. He was named Substate Coach of the Year in 2005.

He will be introduced at halftime of the Class 4A championship game on Friday, March 13.

Class of 2020: Check out the Last Dollar Scholarship

We want to make families aware of a great scholarship opportunity for high school seniors. The Last Dollar Scholarship is a state-funded program that pays tuition and mandatory fees for hundreds of programs offered through Iowa’s community colleges. All students need to do to apply is complete a FAFSA and enroll as a full-time student in the fall. For more information, visit www.iowacollegeaid.gov/LastDollar.

post_text:
ISASP REPORTS COMING HOME
The Iowa Statewide Assessment of Student Progress (ISASP) test results are finally here. Students in grades 3-11 took these tests last March. All students were tested in the areas of math and English language arts, and grades 5, 8, and 10 were tested in science. Mrs. Merkel, our school counselor, will be discussing these results with each grade this week and sending the results home with the students. If you have any questions, please reach out to your child's classroom teacher or Mrs. Merkel.

ATTENTION PRESCHOOL PARENTS
As the winter weather season approaches, we just want to send out a notification reminder that if we have a two-hour delay, preschool will NOT be held that day. All weather announcements will be communicated with local radio stations, television stations WHO13 and KCAU, sent out via text/email through GovDelivery, and communicated on our social media pages. If you have not signed up for our GovDelivery service, you can do so by going to our school webpage under “District” and clicking on “Sign up for school alerts.”

post_text: On Wednesday, October 2, Ar-We-Va students in grades 10-12 will travel to either Iowa State University or Iowa Central Community College for group visits. Dodge will leave around 7:45 and the bus for Ames will leave at 8:00, with both returning before the end of the day. If you have any questions, please e-mail Mrs. Merkel at rmerkel@ar-we-va.k12.ia
